    ZephyrOS — AOSP Source Slimming Manifest (v4, safe)
    Generated from android-14.0.0_r74/default.xml.

    Strategy: ONLY remove device trees, kernel prebuilts, and
    truly optional SDK/emulator/docs projects. Keep ALL test/tool
    platform projects (CTS, VTS, MTS, platform_testing, etc.).
    This avoids the endless "undefined module" Soong errors.

    Disk budget: ~84 GB runner → ~25 GB freed by apt cleanup →
    ~109 GB available. Source ~40 GB + build output ~35 GB = ~75 GB.
    Fit within 109 GB with ~34 GB headroom.

    Safe to remove (device-specific, not needed for GSI):
      - Device trees (Pixel, amlogic, linaro, emulator, etc.)
      - Kernel prebuilts
      - Trusty TEE OS
      - Emulator & SDK tool prebuilts
      - PDK, docs, samples

    MUST keep (referenced by framework/tools):
      - ALL platform/test/*  (CTS, VTS, MTS, csuite, framework, etc.)
      - platform/cts
      - platform/platform_testing
      - device/generic/{arm64,armv7-a-neon,car,uml,x86_64,common,goldfish}
      - device/google/{cuttlefish,gs-common,trout}
      - platform/tools/tradefederation/prebuilts
      - hardware/{interfaces,libhardware,libhardware_legacy,ril}
-->
